{"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"metadata":{"title":"SwiftDataHelpers","modules":[{"name":"SwiftDataHelpers"}],"externalID":"SwiftDataHelpers","symbolKind":"module","roleHeading":"Framework","role":"collection"},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryAdvancedUsage","doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryTesting","doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryPerformance","doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/SwiftDataMigrations"],"anchor":"Guides","title":"Guides"},{"title":"Live Queries","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQuery"],"anchor":"Live-Queries"},{"anchor":"Dependency-Setup","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryBindable","doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/liveQueryContext"],"title":"Dependency Setup"},{"title":"Structures","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/SwiftDataHelpersModelContext"],"anchor":"Structures","generated":true}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftDataHelpers is a small, focused package that collects convenience APIs for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"working with SwiftData in SwiftUI apps. The goal is to keep common patterns"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simple, readable, and testable."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Today the library focuses on live SwiftUI queries powered by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"swift-dependencies","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and it will expand with more helpers over time as new","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"needs appear.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Requirements","text":"Requirements"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"iOS 17, macOS 14, watchOS 10, tvOS 17, visionOS 2"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift tools version 6.2","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"SwiftData (Apple framework, available on the platforms above)","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Dependencies","text":"Dependencies"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-dependencies"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SwiftData (Apple framework)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Get-Started","text":"Get Started"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Add the package in Xcode","anchor":"Add-the-package-in-Xcode"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open your project in Xcode and choose File > Add Packages."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Enter ","type":"text"},{"code":"https:\/\/github.com\/vadimkrutovlv\/swift-data-helpers.git","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Select the ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiftDataHelpers","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" product and add it to your target.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Add the package in Swift Package Manager","anchor":"Add-the-package-in-Swift-Package-Manager"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Package.swift","","dependencies: [","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/vadimkrutovlv\/swift-data-helpers.git\", from: \"1.0.0\")","],","","targets: [","    .target(","        name: \"YourApp\",","        dependencies: [\"SwiftDataHelpers\"]","    )","]"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Update the version as new releases are published.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Using LiveQuery","anchor":"Using-LiveQuery"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LiveQuery"},{"type":"text","text":" is a SwiftUI property wrapper that keeps your view state in sync"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with SwiftData. It refreshes when the underlying model container saves, so your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"lists and sections stay current without manual fetch logic."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It can be thought of as an alternative to SwiftData’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Query"},{"type":"text","text":" macro, with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"explicit dependency-based context configuration."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can also use ","type":"text"},{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Observable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" models (for example, a feature","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"model that owns shared data) and any other main-actor-isolated type where you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"want live SwiftData-backed state.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@LiveQuery"},{"type":"text","text":" inside an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Observable"},{"type":"text","text":" model, mark the property"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@ObservationIgnored"},{"type":"text","text":" to avoid conflicts with the Observation framework:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@Observable","final class MyFeatureModel {","    @ObservationIgnored","    @LiveQuery var items: [Item]","}"],"type":"codeListing"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Configure the ModelContext (primary)","anchor":"Configure-the-ModelContext-primary"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@LiveQuery"},{"type":"text","text":" relies on the Dependencies value "},{"code":"liveQueryContext.modelContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Configure it once at your app entry point so every view has a consistent source"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of truth. This is the recommended setup for most apps."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you do not already have a container, create a main container up front and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"pass its "},{"code":"mainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" into the dependency:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["import Dependencies","import SwiftData","import SwiftDataHelpers","import SwiftUI","","@main","struct MyApp: App {","    let container: ModelContainer = try! ModelContainer(","        for: Person.self","    )","","    init() {","        let container = self.container","        prepareDependencies {","            $0.liveQueryContext.modelContext = { container.mainContext }","        }","    }","","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            ContentView()","                .modelContainer(container)","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"text":"Use @LiveQuery","type":"heading","anchor":"Use-LiveQuery","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@LiveQuery"},{"text":" keeps SwiftUI in sync with SwiftData by refreshing when the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"underlying container saves. You can pass a predicate and sort descriptors to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"filter and order results.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["import SwiftDataHelpers","import SwiftUI","","struct PeopleList: View {","    @LiveQuery(","        predicate: #Predicate<Person> { $0.isActive },","        sort: [SortDescriptor(\\Person.name)]","    )","    private var people: [Person]","","    var body: some View {","        List(people) { person in","            Text(person.name)","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Consume LiveQuery as AsyncStream","anchor":"Consume-LiveQuery-as-AsyncStream","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$people.valuesStream"},{"type":"text","text":" when you need async iteration over snapshots:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["@MainActor","@Observable","final class PeopleFeatureModel {","    @ObservationIgnored","    @LiveQuery(sort: [SortDescriptor(\\Person.name)])","    var people: [Person]","","    @ObservationIgnored","    private var valuesTask: Task<Void, Never>?","","    func observePeople() {","        valuesTask?.cancel()","        valuesTask = Task {","            for await snapshot in $people.valuesStream {","                print(\"People count: \\(snapshot.count)\")","            }","        }","    }","","    deinit {","        valuesTask?.cancel()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Multiple Containers (optional)","anchor":"Multiple-Containers-optional"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your app uses more than one "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ModelContainer"},{"type":"text","text":" (for example, main and private"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"stores), use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryBindable","isActive":true},{"text":" to scope queries to the desired container.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is ideal for subtrees of your UI that should read from a non-default","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"container.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["LiveQueryBindable(modelContainer: .privatePersons) {","    PrivatePeopleView()","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Previews and Tests (optional)","level":3,"anchor":"Previews-and-Tests-optional","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For previews and tests, inject a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ModelContext"},{"text":" directly. This keeps ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@LiveQuery"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"functional without bootstrapping your full app lifecycle.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["#Preview {","    prepareDependencies {","        $0.liveQueryContext.modelContext = { ModelContainer.main.mainContext }","    }","","    return PeopleList()","        .modelContainer(.main)","}"]},{"anchor":"FAQ","type":"heading","text":"FAQ","level":2},{"type":"heading","text":"I see logs about `liveQueryContext.modelContext` not set. What does it mean?","anchor":"I-see-logs-about-liveQueryContextmodelContext-not-set-What-does-it-mean","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" requires a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ModelContext"},{"text":" from","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/Dependencies\/DependencyValues\/liveQueryContext"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If this dependency is not configured, SwiftDataHelpers logs a fault and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"query returns empty results until a context is provided. Configure it once at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"your app entry point with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"prepareDependencies"},{"type":"text","text":", or scope a subtree with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryBindable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Can I use `@LiveQuery` outside of views?","anchor":"Can-I-use-LiveQuery-outside-of-views"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes. It works in "},{"code":"@Observable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" models or other main-actor-isolated types. When"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"used inside an observable model, mark the property wrapper with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@ObservationIgnored"},{"type":"text","text":" to avoid conflicts with Observation."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"How do I query multiple containers?","anchor":"How-do-I-query-multiple-containers"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryBindable"},{"type":"text","text":" to scope queries to a specific container, or override"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the dependency for a particular subtree. The advanced guide shows patterns for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"main\/private container setups.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Is `@LiveQuery` a replacement for `@Query`?","anchor":"Is-LiveQuery-a-replacement-for-Query","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It is an alternative with explicit dependency-based context configuration. If","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"you prefer SwiftData’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Query","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" macro, you can continue using it alongside this","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"library.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage"